raw:
To complete this survey, follow these steps:

1. Select your answer for "trust_coverage" by clicking on one of the radio buttons corresponding to your level of trust in Olympic coverage.
2. Choose an option for "mood_impact" by clicking on one of the radio buttons that best describes how positively the Olympics affected your day-to-day mood.
3. Enter your age into the "age" field, ensuring it falls within the specified range (18 to 99).
4. Select your answer for "follow_by_age" by clicking on one of the radio buttons that best describes how closely you followed the most recent Winter Olympics compared with people in your age group.
5. Choose an option for "employment_status" by clicking on one of the radio buttons that corresponds to your current employment status.
6. Use the slider in the "watch_time" field to select the amount of time you spent daily on Olympics content during the Olympics period. Adjust the slider to a value between 1 and 10, with increments of 1.
7. Select an option for "attention_text_mid" by clicking on one of the radio buttons that best describes your satisfaction with the Olympic coverage you watched or read.
8. Enter your level of satisfaction with your country's Olympic performance in the "country_satisfaction" field, ensuring it falls within the specified range (1 to 10).
9. Choose an option for "future_interest" by clicking on one of the radio buttons that best describes how likely you are to follow the next Olympics.
10. Use the open-ended text field for "favorite_moment" to describe one memorable Olympic moment in your own words.
11. Once all required questions have been answered, click on the "Next" button at the bottom of the page to proceed to the next section of the survey.

Please remember to answer each question before moving to the next one, and ensure that all required fields are filled out completely and accurately. If you need assistance with any specific question or encounter any difficulties while completing the survey, feel free to ask for help!
